quran[27]{c,v,t}:
  17,23,"And thy Lord hath decreed that ye shall Worship none but Him, and unto parents shew kindness; and if either of them or both of them attain old age with thee, Say not unto them: pooh: And browbeat them not, and Speak unto them a respectful speech"
  17,24,"And lower unto them the wing of meekness out of mercy, and say: O my Lord! have mercy on the twain even as they brought me up when young"
  17,25,"Your Lord is the Best Knower of that which is in your souls; if ye have been righteous, then He is unto thee Oftreturning, Forgiving"
  17,26,"And give thou to the kinsman his due, and also unto the needy and the wayfarer; and squander not in squandering"
  17,27,"Verily the squanderers are ever the brethren of the Satans, and the satan is ever unto his Lord ungrateful"
  17,28,"And if thou turnest away from them awaiting a mercy from thy Lord which thou hopest, then speak unto them a gentle speech"
  17,29,"And let not thine hand be chained to thy neck, nor stretch it forth to the utmost stretching, lest thou sit down reproached, impoverished"
  17,30,"Verily thy Lord extendeth the provision for whomsoever He will and He measureth it out; verily He is in respect of His bondmen Aware, Beholder"
  17,31,And saly not your offspring for fear of want; We provide for them and for yourselves; verily their slaying is a great crime
  17,32,And approach not adultery; verily it is ever an abomination and vile as a pathway
  17,33,"And slay not anyone whom Allah hath forbidden except for justification; and whosoever is slain wrongfully, We have surely given his next-of-kin authority so let him not be extravagant in slaying; verily he is ever succoured"
  17,34,"And approach not the substance of an'orphan save with that which is best, until he attaineth his age of strength. And fulfil the covenant; verily the covenant shall be asked about"
  17,35,"And give full measures when ye measure and weigh with an even balance that is good, and the best interpretation"
  17,36,"And go not thou after that where of thou hast no knowledge verily the hearing and the sight and the heart, each of these shall be asked about"
  17,37,"And walk thou not on the earth struttingly; verily thou wilt by no means rend the earth, nor canst thou attain to the mountains in stature"
  17,38,Each of these--theyice thereof is unto thy Lord ever detestable
  17,39,"That is Part of that wisdom which thy Lord hath revealed unto thee, and set not up thou along with Allah anot her god, lest thou be cast into Hell, reproved, rejected"
  17,40,Hath then your Lord distinguished you with sons and taken for Himself females from among the angels? Verily ye say a saying mighty
  17,41,"And assurelly We have propounded it variously in this Qur'an that they might be admonished, but it increaseth them only in aversion"
  17,42,"Say thou: were there along with Him other gods, as they say, then they would have brought unto the Owner of the Throne a way"
  17,43,"Hallowed be He, and exalted be He above that which they say --a greatheight"
  17,44,"There hallow Him the seven heavens and the earth and whosoever is therein. And naught there is but halloweth His praise, but ye understand not their hallowing; verily He is ever Forbearing, Forgiving"
  17,45,"And when thou recitest the Qur'an, We set up between thee and those who believe not in the Hereafter a curtain drawn down"
  17,46,"And We set up over their hearts veils lest they understand it, and in their ears heaviness and when thou mentionest in reciting the Qur'an thy Lord alone, they turn backward as averters"
  17,47,"We are Best Knower of that wherewith they listen what time they listen to thee and what time they counsel together in secret, when the wrong-doers say: ye but follow a man enchanted"
  17,48,Behold! how they propound similitudes for thee! They have strayed and cannot find a way
  17,49,"And they say: when we shall have become bones and fragments, shall we in sooth be raised as a new creation"